Yelnya

Yelnya, a small city 82 km south-east of Smolensk, was conquered by the 10th Panzer Division after heavy figthing on July, 19. Meanwhile parts of the SS division "Das Reich" advanced on Dorogobuzh. Their order was to join Panzer Group 3 (Hoth) to encircle the 16th and 20th Soviet Armies at Smolensk.

Due to the withdrawal of the German 4th Army (von Kluge) to the West and the powerful strength of their 24th Army the Soviets began a counter-offensive in the area of Yelnya ...

